=== Conjuction ===
'''XOR'''
# (Logic) [[Exclusive or]]; either one proposition or the other is true but not both.
# (Computer science) A lexical symbol to implement exclusive or in a computer language.
# (Electrical engineering) A [[logical]] [[gate]] to implement exclusive or.

===Noun===
'''XOR'''
#(Logic) The function ''exclusive or'', true if one and only one of two inputs is true. Expression ''exclusive'' as differ from [[inclusive or|inclusive OR]]. In [[infix notation]], it has values

(0 XOR 0) = 0<br>
(0 XOR 1) = 1<br>
(1 XOR 0) = 1<br>
(1 XOR 1) = 0<br>

